                            <p>
                                To make Ngumbi accessible to as many people as possible, it supports many languages and locales.
                                Of course you can put your links in your own language but more importantly, you can set your
                                search box to use the Google or Yahoo! in your location and for Google you can set the language
                                independently.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                So for example, if you are in India, you can use the google.co.in URL for your
                                search and Hindi (हिंदी) for your language.  You can also mix things up.  For example you can have
                                your search bar using google.com so you'll get google.com search results, but set your language
                                to Filipino to have the search interface in Filipino (Tagalog).  If the Google or Yahoo! search
                                URL that you want to use isn't listed as a choice, you can even enter the one you want manually.
                                The search URL and language that you pick are used no matter what language
                                the computer may be set to.
                            </p>

                            <p>
                                Below is a list of the languages and locations that you can set your ngumbi page's search to use.
                                Let me know if there is one you want but don't see below by using the Contact the Admin link at
                                the bottom.
                            </p>

